</blockquote>


<h1 id="circle-apps-and-libraries">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#circle-apps-and-libraries" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Circle Apps and Libraries
</h1>

<h3 id="pika-backup">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#pika-backup" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Pika Backup <a href="https://apps.gnome.org/app/org.gnome.World.PikaBackup/"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>Keep your data safe.</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@sophieherold:gnome.org">Sophie</a> announces</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Pika Backup now helps with excluding files that are unnecessary to save or too large for backups. The new dialog also provides the option to exclude a single file instead of a complete folder.

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2022/09/twig-59/df55431039cd8b4b7309aad6d692ad47daf2db5c.png" alt="" />
</p>
</blockquote>


<h3 id="amberol">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#amberol" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Amberol <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/ebassi/amberol/"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>Plays music, and nothing else.</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@ebassi:gnome.org">Emmanuele Bassi</a> reports</p>
<blockquote>
<p><a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/World/amberol/-/releases/0.9.1">Amberol 0.9.1 is out</a>, and available of Flathub!</p>
<ul>
<li>Support for ReplayGain metadata in the audio files; Amberol allows you to automatically follow the volume recommendation for track and album if the metadata is available</li>
<li>Support for external cover art files in the same directory as a song</li>
<li>Shuffling now is more reliable, and adding songs to a shuffled playlist will not scramble the existing order</li>
<li>Lots of smaller UI paper cuts, metadata loading fixes, and translation updates

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2022/09/twig-59/5140752b62160e1a8d5d85c94a0a66cb4d4211df.png" alt="" />
</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>


